          "date": "2012-02-21 13:06:58.000000000",
          "tz": -480
        },
        "subject": "LU-974 security: ignore umask if acl enabled",
        "message": "LU-974 security: ignore umask if acl enabled\n\n* add OBD_CONNECT_UMASK to show whether MDS support umask.\n* client ignores umask if acl is enabled.\n* client enforce umask if MDS doesn't support OBD_CONNECT_UMASK to\n  make new client act the same as old client with old MDS server.\n* client packs umask for create/open, and if default acl doesn't exist,\n  MDS will enforce this umask in ldiskfs inode creation.\n* don't clear current->fs->umask on MDS, because ldiskfs will use it\n  in inode creation.\n\nChange-Id: I4adb5418cc5d7a3dee60c74ec75e65aaeb14e035\nSigned-off-by: Lai Siyao <laisiyao@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b1_8"
    }
  },
